#. <section class="sutta" id="sn15.6"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn15.6:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 15"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn15.6:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn15.6:0.3"
msgid "6. Sāsapasutta"
msgstr ""

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn15.6:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn15.6:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yena bhagavā … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so "
"bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn15.6:1.3"
msgid "“kīvadīgho nu kho, bhante, kappo”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn15.6:1.4"
msgid "“Dīgho kho, bhikkhu, kappo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn15.6:1.5"
msgid ""
"So na sukaro saṅkhātuṃ ettakāni vassāni iti vā … pe … ettakāni "
"vassasatasahassāni iti vā”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn15.6:2.1"
msgid "“Sakkā pana, bhante, upamaṃ kātun”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn15.6:2.2"
msgid "“Sakkā, bhikkhū”ti bhagavā avoca."
msgstr ""

# BB follows the comm in saying the city has iron walls. Not unreasonable, but it’s not what the text says. As for gulikabaddha, BB evidently reads culika and translates “dense as a topknot”, which doesn’t make much sense. PTS dict has “put together, kneaded, made into cakes (of meal )” as a meaning of baddha, and this is clearly preferable here.
#. VAR: guḷikābaddhaṃ → cūḷikābaddhaṃ (bj) | guḷikābandhaṃ (s1-3) | cuḷikābaddhaṃ (pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn15.6:2.3"
msgid ""
"“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhu, āyasaṃ nagaraṃ yojanaṃ āyāmena yojanaṃ vitthārena "
"yojanaṃ ubbedhena, puṇṇaṃ sāsapānaṃ guḷikābaddhaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn15.6:2.4"
msgid ""
"Tato puriso vassasatassa vassasatassa accayena ekamekaṃ sāsapaṃ uddhareyya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn15.6:2.5"
msgid ""
"Khippataraṃ kho so, bhikkhu, mahāsāsaparāsi iminā upakkamena parikkhayaṃ "
"pariyādānaṃ gaccheyya, na tveva kappo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn15.6:2.6"
msgid "Evaṃ dīgho kho, bhikkhu, kappo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn15.6:2.7"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ dīghānaṃ kho, bhikkhu, kappānaṃ neko kappo saṃsito, nekaṃ kappasataṃ "
"saṃsitaṃ, nekaṃ kappasahassaṃ saṃsitaṃ, nekaṃ kappasatasahassaṃ saṃsitaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn15.6:2.8"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn15.6:2.9"
msgid "Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhu, saṃsāro … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn15.6:2.10"
msgid "alaṃ vimuccitun”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn15.6:2.11"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
